  "prompt": "What is Instagram's hourly comment limit?",
  "response": "Instagram doesn\u2019t publicly disclose a specific hourly comment limit, but it enforces limits to prevent spam and abusive behavior. These limits are based on factors like account age, activity, and behavior. Generally, users report that commenting too frequently (e.g., more than 20\u201330 comments per hour) can trigger action blocks or warnings.\n\nTo avoid issues:\n\n1. **Avoid rapid-fire commenting**: Space out your comments naturally.\n2. **Engage genuinely**: Comments should be relevant and thoughtful.\n3. **Respect community guidelines**: Avoid spammy or repetitive behavior.\n\nIf you're temporarily blocked from commenting, take a break and reduce your activity. Persistent issues may lead to longer restrictions or account suspension. Always follow Instagram\u2019s guidelines to stay safe.",
